FBIS3-47810 "dreas012_c_94011" FBIS-EAS-94-012 Document Type:Daily Report 19 Jan 1994 North Korea PRC's Jiang Zemin Assures Hwang of Friendship SK1801050794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0452 GMT 18 Jan 94 SK1801050794 Pyongyang KCNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Pyongyang, January 18 (KCNA) -- It is a firm stand of China to strengthen and develop the China-Korea friendship and no one can change it. China would, as always, do its utmost for the development of traditional ties between China and Korea and make tireless efforts toward the consolidation and development of the exchange and cooperation between the two countries in different domains. Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China and president of China, made the remarks in a meeting with Hwang Chang-yop, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, and his entourage in Beijing Monday. Noting that the ties between the two countries of China and Korea is different from that between other countries, he said the China-Korea friendship was tied with blood and founded and fostered by Comrades Mao Zedong and Zhou Enlai together with Comrade Kim Il-song.
